{"key":"processedPost-13128010","value":{"id":13128010,"first":13123298,"last":13128170,"when":1283266460,"utime":"08/31/10 05:54 PM","content":"<blockquote>Quote:<br /><b>uninc4life2010 said:</b><br />My substrate doesn't seem to be drying out, it appears fairly cottony, with very small beads of condensation every here and there on the surface.&nbsp; I have had big problems in the past with oversaturation and water pooling, making me feel a little nervous about misting<br /></blockquote><br /><br />Fresh air is the number 1 pinning trigger.&nbsp; If you have sufficient FAE, you won't have the problems you listed above.&nbsp; You need more air exchange.&nbsp; After misting, all standing water droplets on the substrate and fruits should be gone within 15 minutes.&nbsp; If not, you don't have enough fresh air supply.<br /><br />I spray my outdoor blocks down with a water hose with a spray attachment, and it knocks the hell out of them.&nbsp; Sometimes it rolls the substrate blocks over from the force.&nbsp; It doesn't cause aborts.&nbsp; Lack of fresh air causes aborts.<br />RR","title":"Re: Should I still mist once Primordia/Pins show? I have heard otherwise","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}